The arm tattoo design if of the Assassin’s emblem, flanked by angelic wings with a Mjolnir sign in the center. Two griffons spread out from a decorative hidden blade that points to a sigil of various runes. Below is a spear that pierces through a series of roots, into two longships facing outwards.

An Assassin’s Creed Valhalla-themed frame around a fan-made tattoo design. The design is by @OuterDesert on Instagram. The head tattoo design covers the forehead, leaving while linework reminiscent of an astral star map. The lines curve with the contours of the head and three dots on either side flank a line that goes from the bridge of the nose straight to the back of the head.

An Assassin’s Creed Valhalla-themed frame around a fan-made tattoo design. The design is by @Le_Papillon08 on Instagram. The back tattoo design is of Fenrir, reared up on his hind legs and turning back to the left, mouth open in a roar. The wolf is comprised of intricate, interlocking knots, hairs, ties, and shading details.

An Assassin’s Creed Valhalla-themed frame around a fan-made tattoo design. The design is by @Elfydil on Twitter. The front torso tattoo design prominently features a raven skull pierced by a dagger, surrounded by thorn-covered vines and patterned serpents that end in fearsome wolf-heads. The collarbones of the design include two wolf skulls with open mouths facing a sun-like symbol.

A piece of Assassin's Creed Valhalla concept art, showing a sun-bathed, verdant hilltop populated by a stone-circle fort. Smoke rises from three small structures; a larger and smaller hut and a partially obstructed overhang. The stone circle has one entryway that opens to a grassy walkway, sloping towards a wooden gate. A hooded figure rides a horse up the path.
